    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Asplenium mohillense are antioxidant, antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and anticancer activities. The plant's antioxidant properties, mediated by flavonoids and phenolic acids, help protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Asplenium mohillense's antimicrobial activity, attributed to saponins and volatile oils, inhibits the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, thereby preventing infections. The plant's anti-inflammatory properties, due to the presence of sesquiterpenes and flavonoids, reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with conditions such as arthritis and other inflammatory diseases. Additionally, the anticancer properties of Asplenium mohillense, associated with the bioactivity of glycosides and phenolic compounds, have been shown to inhibit cancer cell proliferation and induce apoptosis.",
