    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Asplenium mohillense are flavonoids, terpenoids, and phenolic acids, which have been identified as the primary bioactive compounds responsible for its medicinal properties. Flavonoids, specifically isorhapontigenin, have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial activities. Terpenoids, including sesquiterpenes and diterpenes, have been found to possess antimicrobial, antifungal, and anticancer properties. Phenolic acids, particularly caffeic and ferulic acids, have been reported to possess antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities. The combination of these constituents in Asplenium mohillense is likely responsible for its traditional uses in treating various health conditions, including wound healing, inflammation, and infection.",
