    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Asplenium mohillense are derived from its rhizome and leaves, which are rich in bioactive compounds. As a medicinal plant, the rhizome and leaves can be made into a tea by infusing them in hot water to create an aqueous extract that is rich in antioxidants and anti-inflammatory compounds. The leaves can also be used to make an infusion by steeping them in cold water, which is said to be beneficial for digestive issues. A tincture can be prepared by soaking the rhizome and leaves in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, creating a concentrated liquid extract that can be used to treat a range of health issues. Additionally, the leaves can be made into a salve or decoction by combining them with a carrier oil or water and applying topically to treat skin issues or as a digestive aid.",
